Donna Summer was more than one of the disco era's most successful artists. 
She earned a string of hits throughout the Seventies and Eighties with her innovative songwriting and powerful, sensual voice that has influenced dance music for decades. 
From the rough-and-tumble of "I FEEL LOVE" to the triumphant anthem (and wedding favorite) "HOT STAFF," and many moving ballads in between, Summer helped define the magic of the dance floor all over the world.
